In this documentation page, under "Using an init.d script", step 3, there is a script example of "/etc/init.d/stash"

https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/STASH/Running+Stash+as+a+Linux+service

This code is wrong where it says:

{code}
"export STASH_HOME=${STASH_HOME};${STASH_INSTALLDIR}/bin/$1"
{code}

It should be

{code}
export STASH_HOME="${STASH_HOME}";"${STASH_INSTALLDIR}/bin/$1"
{code}

Now Stash detect only Conflicts from Automerge, but if we start to commit unresolved conflicts as is into repository, Stash will not detect them.

Will be nice to have property in stash-config.properties:
{code}
conflict.marker.size=250
{code}
Also you must rewrite DiffOutputHandler and ConflictHandlingPullRequestMergeHandler.

This would most likely look something _like_:

{code}
public interface Settings {
    Settings onSave(Settings oldSettings, SettingsBuilder settings);
    Settings onLoad(SettingsBuilder settings);
}
{code}

This would allow, for example, to encrypt and decrypt a settings value before being saved and loaded from the database.

