Regarding the discussion on STASH-2521 about multiple hooks, it would be nice to be able to ship duplicate hooks, but have them be disabled unless user explicitly needs more than one. This avoids cluttering the web hook settings display with unnecessary duplicates. For example, Confluence macros can be shipped disabled with something like
{noformat}
enabled="false"
{noformat}

Please document user directory limitations that prevents a user from editing a directory config if they belong to the same directory. 
JIRA has this well [documented|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+User+Directories#ConfiguringUserDirectories-UpdatingDirectories]:
{quote}
You cannot edit, disable or remove the directory your user belongs to. This precaution is designed to prevent administrators from locking themselves out of the application by changing the directory configuration in a way that prevents them logging in or removes their administration permissions.

This limitation applies to all directory types.
{quote}

